<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="18Feb1927"><font color="red">18 February 1927</font> <i>Selected Letters</i> (to Harriet Weaver): I want the case of Pound&apos;s soundness of judgement at the present moment more gone into. I am glad you agree about Dunning &hellip; I am working on but in a grumbling quarter convinced way. I am sorry the piece gave you no pleasure. It was hard when writing it to keep myself at the right pitch and perhaps it suffered. </div>
